This paper is primarily focused on the design and planning of computer networks, specifically in a wider geographical area. This falls under the category of Network and Communications (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the calculation of relevant parameters and the cost of technology and services, which could fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper also mentions the use of indicators of socioeconomic status, which could fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
